arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a logistics shipment tracking Blazor Web App. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-421043ad01c242539b002d341da71e78/ShipmentTracker/` using `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

## Project Structure
- **ShipmentTracker/** (server project) — hosts the app, has EF Core, Identity, etc.
- **ShipmentTracker.Client/** (WebAssembly project) — all interactive components go here.
- This is **Auto mode, Global** — components run on Server first visit, WebAssembly on subsequent visits.
- **Critical rule**: Interactive components MUST live in `.Client` project. They CANNOT directly access DbContext. All data access from interactive components must go through HTTP APIs.

## What to Implement

### 1. Shared Models (in `.Client` project so both server and WASM can use them)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentStatus.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}
```

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentDto.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string RecipientEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public double WeightKg { get; set; }
}
```

### 2. Service Interface (in `.Client` project)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsAsync();
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id);
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment);
    Task<ShipmentDto> UpdateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment);
    Task DeleteShipmentAsync(int id);
}
```

### 3. Client-side HTTP Implementation (in `.Client` project)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient httpClient) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>($"api/shipments/{id}");
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>($"api/shipments/track/{Uri.EscapeDataString(trackingNumber)}");
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>())!;
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> UpdateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{shipment.Id}", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>())!;
    }

    public async Task DeleteShipmentAsync(int id)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.DeleteAsync($"api/shipments/{id}");
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
    }
}
```

### 4. Server-side Data Model and DbContext

Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/Shipment.cs` (EF entity — server project only):
```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }

    [Required, MaxLength(20)]
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required, MaxLength(200)]
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required, MaxLength(200)]
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public int Status { get; set; }

    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }

    [Required, MaxLength(100)]
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [MaxLength(200)]
    public string RecipientEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [MaxLength(500)]
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public double WeightKg { get; set; }
}
```

Update `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;

